      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__v__mix_1ga11c3c9f8be66807a720a0043195e5382" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void XVMix_InterruptHandler</definition>
        <argsstring>(void *InstancePtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XVMix_InterruptHandler</name>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function is the interrupt handler for the mixer core driver. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This handler clears the pending interrupt and determined if the source is frame done signal. If yes, starts the next frame processing and calls the registered callback function</para><para>The application is responsible for connecting this function to the interrupt system. Application beyond this driver is also responsible for providing callbacks to handle interrupts and installing the callbacks using <ref refid="group__v__mix_1gad12afb12681e1426a8129e35fa729046" kindref="member">XVMix_SetCallback()</ref> during initialization phase.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the core instance that just interrupted.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
